1. Once upon a time there was a man who had five sons.\
\
2. Every day all they did was quarrel with each other.\
\
3. What one would say the other wouldn\'92t listen to.\
\
4. So having seen this, their father said to them:\
\
5. \'93My boys, every day you quarrel with each other.\'94\
\
6. \'93 You don\'92t get along with one another.\'94\
\
7. \'93Break off a stick from a tree and bring it to me.\'94\
\
8. \'93Each one of you break one off and bring it to me,\'94 he said.\
\
9. Then, as their father had told them to, the sons broke them off and carried them off to where their father was. [1]\
\
10. \'93Now each of you try to bend and snap the sticks you broke off,\'94 he said.\
\
11. At this point, when the sticks they had each broken off were bent, they immediately snapped 
