\
13. Having sent all his sons to go back again to break off [sticks] to carry back, they set them down before \
      their father.\
\
14. This time the father tied them nicely together, then he had them bend [the bundle], one after the other.\
\
15. Even though one [son] after the other bent it, it wouldn\'92t snap.\
\
16. Then the father said, \'93My sons, if each of you stays by himself, just the same as a while ago, with \
      the breaking of those sticks, you will be destroyed.  You will have to fail [in life],\'94 he said.\
\
17. \'93But just as when you bent them again this time, if you all stick together and are united in feelings \
      with each other [3], even if others should try to harm you, you will not be destroyed,\'94 he said.\
\
18. Well, it\'92s just the same with us Christians too.\
\
19. If we put our trust in the Lord Jesus Christ, we will achieve everlasting life. [4].\
\
20. If we do not place faith in the Lord Jesus Christ, we will fall into temptations to sin.\
\
21. Therefore I would like to sing a little song about how if we put our trust in the lord Jesus Christ, the \
      Precious Son of God, [5] we will achieve everlasting life:\
\
22. [sings] Do welcome gladly God\'92s Precious Son,\
	        And you will win Life Eternal.\
